    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-27T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-27T09:00:00-05:00" n="491"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">671.116/28: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania (<persName type="from"
                            >Owsley</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-27T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 27, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. Department’s December 20, 1 p.m. Allotment import quota licenses improved,
                    officials indicate important favorable changes pending. Full report by mail will
                    be forwarded after further consultation with proper authorities. Strongly urge
                    no liquor quota agreement pending receipt of full report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Owsley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
